A rider had a miraculous escape after their horse slipped into a steep muddy ditch and became trapped for two hours.

The unhurt rider clambered out of the ditch near the village of Harringworth, Northamptonshire, but firefighters had to use special winching equipment to rescue the horse which was trapped on its side.

A Northamptonshire Fire & Rescue Service crew from Corby used an animal rescue harness to help free the adult horse from the ditch, which was muddy following the recent wet weather.

