A specialist animal rescue unit from Wellingborough, Northamptonshire, also helped to rescue the horse, which slipped into the ditch at around 11am on Sunday.

A spokesman for the fire service said: ‘It was a large horse measuring 17.3 hands and the sides of the ditch were steep. Its rider was able to get out uninjured and called the vet straight away.’

The horse was also uninjured and after a short rest the owner walked it back to its stables.

